{
  "id": "sages_council",
  "encounterTitle": "Sage's Counsel",
  "description": "A ruined imperial ward-complex outside the city — a struck-off Cape shelters in the last standing sanctum, and she knows what happened to Vael.",
  "mapId": "isolated_ruin",
  "npcIds": [
    "eryn_cault"
  ],
  "allyIds": [],
  "enemyIds": [],
  "customIntroduction": "The ruins open under a bruised sky: two fallen watchtowers, a collapsed hall, and at the far north a sanctum still half-roofed. A thin line of smoke rises from inside it — wood-smoke, and fresh. Someone has been here, and not long ago. You pick your way in across the rubble.",
  "customContext": "The Sundered Circuit is a ruined Imperial ward-complex — toppled watchtowers, a collapsed hall, and a half-roofed sanctum at the north end where Eryn Cault keeps a fire. Cault is a struck-off Cape, decades older than Reed, living rough for years: tired, guilty, not unkind — what the capital's indifference makes when it runs long enough. The CONVERSATION tree owns her lore and releases it in layers (deeper truths behind Insight/Persuasion DC 12–14) — let patience and good questions matter as much as the roll, and don't pre-empt what she has to say.\n\nThe ruins reward searching as the talk unfolds. On the approach into the sanctum a dedication stone, half-buried in masonry, names the ward-binding rite Reed will need at the keystone — the scene's most valuable find, a gift from the past to the finale. By the fire, Vael's licence-seal lies in the ash, confirming he was here and did not leave the way he came. A cache in a collapsed wall holds a healing draught for whoever looks.\n\nThe scene closes with Cault giving Reed the way down and a plain warning: no one will certify this for her. For the first time, she acts on her own authority.",
  "objective": "Search the ruined ward-complex — someone still keeps a fire here. Learn what became of Senior Cape Vael and what the wardstones truly need, and find the way down.",
  "completionFlag": "sage_way_down_given",
